# Go + Fly.io .gitignore — adapted from Go module + Fly.io CLI conventions
# in Phase 26 (D-08). Template-only — operators may extend for project-specific
# paths. Phase 24 openrouter-monitor precedent does NOT apply directly here
# (different runtime); this file follows Go module conventions and Fly.io
# local config conventions (ASSUMED — Phase 26 RESEARCH A3).

# Compiled test binaries.
*.test

# Coverage output.
*.out

# Vendored dependencies (if `go mod vendor` is used).
vendor/

# Fly.io CLI: flyctl stores config in $HOME/.fly (user-level), NOT a repo-local
# .fly/ — see https://community.fly.io/t/flyctl-should-follow-the-xdg-base-directory-specification/1743
# and the flyctl config-init source. The original ASSUMED .fly/ entry from Phase 26
# RESEARCH A3 was removed in this PR's CodeRabbit pass (PR #60) — no repo-local
# .fly/ directory exists to ignore. Left as a header comment so operators aren't
# surprised when their flyctl creds don't show up in this project.

# Common Go build/temp.
tmp/

# Secrets — NEVER commit (some Go projects use these envvar shapes too).
.env
.env.local
